<dl id="n09022h"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n09" href="#n09022h">N09 (VI.B.1)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n09all.htm#n09022h"> 22(h)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> nasty blunt club</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><b>Correspondence. / The Inland Waterways of Saorstat Eireann</b>. &hellip; As I listened to the debate on the motion that immediate effect shall be given to the Recommendations of the Inland Waterways Commission my spirits sank lower and lower &hellip; it was the manner of the rejection rather than the rejection itself which depressed my spirits, for it was impossible to avoid the reflection that this is the manner in which every constructive proposal will be treated if it involves the least effort to overcome current financial difficulties.&hellip; The Railway Bill must provide for a Rates Tribunal, and the Waterway Report recommends a single Tribunal for both systems of transport. But, no; the whole Report, all the hopes of the by-traders and merchants on the waterways, were just smashed with a nasty blunt club. <small> <a name="IS23feb24" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#IS23feb24"><cite title="source">Irish Statesman</cite></a> (23 February 1924) 747/2</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c03068e" href="c03all.htm#c03068e">VI.C.03:068(e)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
